					<tr><th align=center bgcolor=#CCC>Some Important stuffs for Linux Geeks</th></tr>
					<tr><td bgcolor=#EEE>1 .Install libgraph library in GCC (Graphics.h)
						<p>Step #1.Install the following in Synaptic Package Manager</p>
						<ol>
							<li><i>libsdl-image1.2</li>
							<li>libsdl-image1.2-dev</li>
							<li>guile-1.8</li>
							<li>guile-1.8-dev</i></li>
						</ol>
						<p>Step #2. Download and install <a href="http://download.savannah.nongnu.org/releases/libgraph/libgraph-1.0.1.tar.gz" target="_blank">libgraph</a> then
						<ol>
							<li><i>./configure</li>
							<li>sudo make</li>
							<li>sudo make install</i></li>
						</ol>								
					</td></tr>	
					<tr><td bgcolor=#FFF><br>	
						2. Install LAMP (Linux-Apache-Mysql-PHP) in a single command 
						<ol>
							<li><i>sudo  apt-get install apache2 php5 libapache2-mod-php5 mysql-server php5-mysql</i></li>
						</ol>
					</td></tr>
					<tr><td bgcolor=#EEE>	
						3 .Some of the things to do immediately after installing ubuntu on your machine:</b><br>
						<ol>
							<li><i>Linux DC++ Client : sudo apt-get install linuxdcpp</li>
							<li>Adobe Acrobat Reader : sudo aptitude install acroread acroread-plugins acroread-escrip</li>
							<li>Macromedia Flash : sudo apt-get install flashplugin-nonfree</li>
							<li>Acroread plugin for firefox : sudo aptitude install mozilla-acroread</li>
							<li>Installing Sun Java JRE : sudo aptitude install sun-java6-jre sun-java6-plugin sun-java6-fonts<i></li>
						</ol>
					</td></tr>
					<tr><td bgcolor=#FFF>	
						4 .Install Gnome classic theme in 11.04+ (who dont like <u>Gnome Unity</u>)</b><br>
						<ol>
							<li><i>Command : sudo apt-get install gnome-session-fallback</li>
							<li>To make Gnome Classic as default : sudo /usr/lib/lightdm/lightdm-set-defaults -s gnome-classic<i></li>
							
						</ol>
					</td></tr>
